To create a custom template in Logic follow these steps.

1. Assign any [[Logic:_Creating_a_screenset|key commands]] you wish to use.

2. [[Logic:Create_a_new_track|Add the tracks]] you wish to use in your template such as audio, [[software instrument]] or [[Logic:_Create_Aux_send|Aux's or busses]] and set the I/O configuration for them.

3. Add any plug ins you wish to use.

4. Click '''File''' then '''Save Template As''' and then save your template in Logic's '''Project Template''' folder.

[[File:Logic save as template.png]]


You should now be able access the template when started a new session in Logic.




